Visual C# 2017 00369-60000-00001-AA127
Microsoft Visual C# 2017

C# 7.2

**Steps to Reproduce**:

Compile and inspect IL:
```
using System;

readonly struct S
{
    readonly decimal d;

    public S(decimal d)
    {
        this.d = d;
    }
}

class P
{
    static void Foo(in S? x)
    {
        Console.WriteLine(x.GetValueOrDefault());
    }
    
    static void Main()
    {
        S? y = new S(5m);
        Foo(y);
    }
}
```
**Actual Behavior**:
The `in` parameter `x` in the method  `Foo` is copied to a compiler-generated local before `GetValueOrDefault()` is invoked.

**Expected Behavior**:
This copy is unnecessary and should be elided. No method or property of a nullable value type can mutate it if the underlying type is a readonly struct.

