   at Program.F(DateTime& x) in Program.cs:line 7

VB's current case-mapping rules for identifier equivalence uses a pretty old version of the Unicode spec, and has bugs. Specifically we use the "invariant" locale, which because it is invariant will never change to be updated as the Unicode spec evolves.

We should instead use a "neutral" culture for the case-mapping, such as the "en" locale, which follows the Unicode case-mapping rules and has no locale-specific exceptions.

